 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B \to  A]]></fr:tex> be a section of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>; if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0]]></fr:tex> is the centre of contraction of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, then the centre of contraction of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is given by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ra_0]]></fr:tex>. For the rest, we use <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0026.xml" title="Propositions are closed under retracts" addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
